  "gaps": [
    { "want": "generic log-workout ('i did a 45 minute bike ride', 'logged a swim', 'did an hour of yoga')", "needs": "new log-workout skill: the workout type already has an 'activity' text attribute, but only log-run/log-walk exist and they hardcode activity; need a skill taking {activity, distance, duration} inputs plus corpus templates" },
    { "want": "runs in miles ('did a 3 mile run', 'ran 2 miles')", "needs": "unit conversion: log-run stores distance as km; quantity slot or skill needs mile->km handling before mile templates are safe to add" },
    { "want": "water in glasses/cups/oz with a count ('had 3 cups of water', 'drank 2 glasses')", "needs": "hydration.amount is ml; a '3 cups' template would log 3 ml; needs unit-aware quantity or a glassCount input with ml conversion in the water template DSL" },
    { "want": "cumulative water state ('i'm at 6 glasses today')", "needs": "set-total semantics, not additive logging; needs a new skill (set-water-today) or DSL support for replace-today aggregation" },
    { "want": "steps today query ('how many steps today', 'what's my step count today')", "needs": "steps.json only ships steps-this-week; needs a steps-today skill in templates/steps.json" },
    { "want": "weight queries ('what's my weight trend', 'what did i weigh last week', 'am i losing weight')", "needs": "weight.json ships log-weight only; needs query skills (last-weight, weight-trend)" },
    { "want": "bare mood statements ('i'm exhausted', 'kind of down', 'i'm happy')", "needs": "an open 'i'm {rating:text}' template would swallow 'i'm going to...', 'i'm 180 lbs' etc.; needs a closed-set mood-adjective slot type in the DSL to match safely" },
    { "want": "meal type capture ('had eggs for breakfast' storing mealType=breakfast)", "needs": "meal type has no mealType attribute and log-meal has no such input; breakfast/lunch/dinner words are currently discarded; schema + skill change to store it" },
    { "want": "list today's meals ('what did i eat today', 'what have i had today')", "needs": "no list-meals skill exists; calories-today only returns a total" },
    { "want": "calorie budget ('how many calories do i have left today')", "needs": "no calorie goal concept; needs a set-calorie-goal skill + remaining-calories query" },
    { "want": "run with route ('ran the river loop', 'log a run and how far')", "needs": "workout type has no route attribute; schema + log-run input change" },
    { "want": "custom exercise trackers ('i did 20 pushups', 'did 3 sets of squats')", "needs": "no pushups/strength tracker template exists; this is the paid template-authoring path, not a corpus addition" }
  ],
  "notes": "COLLISIONS/ORDERING: (1) log-meal's existing greedy 'i had {food:text}' overlaps water ('i had a glass of water'), meds ('i had my morning pills'), and the new 'i had {food:text} for lunch' variants — the router must rank longer/more-literal templates (glass/water/pills/meds/for-lunch anchors) above the bare meal template, otherwise food gets polluted ('a glass of water', 'a sandwich for lunch' -> failed calorie lookup). Same for 'i ate {food} for lunch' vs existing 'i ate {food}'. (2) Deliberately did NOT add bare 'i'm {rating:text}' or '{food:text}' — unanchored, would swallow unrelated 'i'm ...' intents; 'feeling {rating:text}' is the loosest mood anchor added and could still capture 'feeling like ordering pizza' (acceptable: still mood-adjacent, and specific templates should outrank it). (3) 'i'm {value:quantity} lbs today' is safe because the lbs/kg literal anchors it away from log-mood. (4) Water additions are ml-or-unitless only; glass-count phrasings withheld pending unit conversion (see gaps). (5) Weight unit words (lbs/kg/pounds) are matched but not stored — value logs as a bare number, consistent with the existing skill. (6) 'did a {distance:quantity}k' / 'went for a {distance:quantity}k' rely on the literal 'k' suffix as anchor. All additions verified non-duplicate against corpus.json, corpus-learned.json, and each template's bundled corpus array as of this session."
}
